metadata.name: Absorbed #137
metadata.description:
A collaboration between leading British high-end audio brand KEF, generative artist hieroglyphica, and creative studio Parameta, Absorbed embodies the process of noise becoming high-fidelity sound through KEF’s Metamaterial Absorption Technology (MAT™). 

MAT™ makes the KEF sound what it is: absorbing unwanted distortion to deliver pure, accurate sound exactly as the artist intended. Inspired by this intricacy, Absorbed illustrates pseudorandom networks of patterns, slowly emerging and transforming into the maze-like form of MAT™. Clarity is revealed, noise is absorbed – high-fidelity is found.

The noise fields used in Absorbed are of two distinct types: conventional gradient noise and “sinusoidal” noise, an original algorithm developed for this series. The use of animation as artistic medium reflects the artists’ belief that no single frame can capture the full range of complexity found in the tension between sound and noise, and lets collectors observe for themselves this ever-shifting dialogue. A more extensive discussion of the algorithms used in Absorbed can be found in hieroglyphica’s companion article on fx(text).

- spacebar will pause and resume the animation
- s will save a still image of the current frame
- technically minded collectors can consult the index.html file for info on how to render and save high-resolution images
- use of hardware acceleration in Chrome may impact performance

Founded by BBC engineer Raymond Cooke in 1961, KEF is a leading British innovator of high-end audio products including HiFi speakers, subwoofers, architectural speakers, wireless speaker-systems, and headphones. Find out more at kef.com or visit our Discord at discord.com/invite/u48Z9yjY2q.

metadata.name: Pine Dream #52
metadata.description:
Pine dream by Asaf Slook (2022)

This work is an attempt to create a simple pen-like generated drawing, in a way that confuses the observer to perceive it to be a real unique hand-drawn piece.

Rare features:
- Lonely tree
- Static stroke
- Sunny day palette
- Dotted land
- Partial land
 
The best results are from 1000x1000 and above.

This work was created using p5.js and love :)

metadata.name: fx(haish) / the Generator #112
metadata.description:
fx(haish) is my contribution to #fxhashturnsone
fx(haish) is not a finished product
fx(haish) is a co-creation experiment
fx(haish) is a fun exploration of a mixed GenAI process

fx(haish) is my Happy Birthday to fx(hash). 

Have fun, collectors!


// HOW TO PARTICIPATE

Step 1. Mint or collect “fx(haish) - the Generator”
Step 2. Visit https://www.arqtistic.com/fx(haish) to generate your “fx(haish) - The AI City” based on your mint. You have 20 tries.
Step 3. Await further instructions.


// FURTHER INFO

This algorithm has been designed to produce images which are suitable for the subsequent AI generation. The token consists of a random number of randomly placed and sized rectangles, filled with a noise gradient pattern. In short, Diffusion AI Models thrive on noise.

The AI generation uses Stable Diffusion 1.5 through an API designed by the 330ai team (@Pixelmindai). The WebUI has been developed by Nik0gda (@AntonCebanu2). AI Prompt has been designed (by me) to produce images of Cities, but you can possibly make it do other things, if you try hard enough.

metadata.name: Rain Ritual #133
metadata.description:
Every windy gust.... every breeze, gave the restless grasses a chance to spread their suggestive rumours, their spurious gossip. All the while, Old Ones of the field towered above, chanting to their wrathful Sky God for more rain.... Always more rain. 

Instructions 
Intended for high resolutions. Use the following keys once render is complete, to export (letters export without a border) 

Square mode 
   1 (q) : 2048x2048  
   2 (w) : 3072x3072 
   3 (e) : 4096x4096 
   4 (r) : 5120x5120 

Landscape mode (increases spacing between objects to preserve aspect ratio) 
   5 (t) : 2560x1440 
   6 (y) : 3840x2160 
   7 (u) : 5128x2880 
   8 (I) : 7680x4320 

Note: Generated textures are resolution dependant, resulting in very slight differences across resolutions. Composition however, remains identical. 

Browsers 
Tested with Chrome, Edge and Firefox on Windows, Chrome on Mac. 
Note for Firefox users : Ensure "Use hardware acceleration" is ticked – Found in Settings / Performance. Other advanced settings to enable include : gfx.canvas.accelerated,  gfx.direct2d.force-enabled and gfx.offscreencanvas.enabled - Unfortunately even with these, Firefox appears slower than other browsers.

metadata.name: Tangentum #209
metadata.description:
We live in a multiverse: an infinite-dimensional space of variants. Everything exists here. Everything is possible. Each subset of a multiverse has its own unique laws of physics, a set of rules, and its own distinct features.

Tangentum creates a projection of a random multiverse subset to a 2-dimensional plane. Each variation is a unique representation of the force field, that exists somewhere at some point in time.

This work starts a series of my visual exploration of functions, continuity, and boundedness, and I would love to share it with you.


Please use fullscreen or download artwork in high resolution for a better viewing experience.

Tested with Chrome 107, Safari, and Firefox. Chrome is recommended, other browsers are slower on this artwork.

Saving with high and ultra-high resolution may take a while, please be patient.


Made with love and p5js


Controls in fullscreen:
[1] - save PNG 2700 x 1800
[2] - save PNG 5400 x 3800
[3] - save PNG 10800 x 7600
[4] - save PNG 16200 x 11400

metadata.name: k3rnel #77
metadata.description:
Self-organizing future-jazz geometry for like-minded pixel based neighbourhoods. 


********
Glossary
********

'Self-organization' → the process by which individuals organize their communal behaviour to create global order by interactions amongst themselves rather than through external intervention or instruction.

'Future-jazz-geometry' → propulsive syncopated visual rhythms, polyphonic ensemble playing, varying degrees of improvisation, and often deliberate distortions of pitch and timbre.

'Like-minded' → sharing the same opinions, ideas, or interests. 

'Pixel' → the smallest addressable element in an all points addressable display device; so it is the smallest controllable element of a picture represented on the screen.

'Neighbourhood' → a spatial unit, in which face-to-face social interactions occur.

Touch to listen, go fullscreen

metadata.name: Project 420 #19
metadata.description:
Project 420 is a minimalist work created with p5.js where the goal was to create the shortest possible project (while being deterministic, responsive, nice and relatively complex).

The project code is only 420 characters long!

let f=0,r,l,e,t=i=>{++f>30||(l=99/f**.8,k=[],i.forEach((j=>[[-1,0],[0,-1],[1,0],[0,1]].forEach((o=>f<4|e()<.27&&k.push([j[0]+l*o[0],j[1]+l*o[1]]))))),k.forEach((i=>stroke(...e()<.5?[75,75,75]:[z,z,z],e(z))&circle(i[0]*y,i[1]*y,e(l/10,l)*y))),t(k))},y,z=255;function setup(){randomSeed(1e8*fxrand()),r=min(windowWidth,windowHeight),createCanvas(r,r),y=r/z/2,e=random,strokeWeight(.8*y),noFill(),background(33),t([[z,z]])}

Code is art ✨

metadata.name: Ramble #25
metadata.description:
ram•ble - talk or write at length in a confused or inconsequential way / a walk taken for pleasure in the countryside

Ramble is narrative artwork about a life (or lives). From a single observation to a long history. Part prose part painting. After a time the letters of the narrative slowly cover with tiny abstract landscapes. They are the type of landscape painting you would paint on a postage stamp. As the size of the narrative grows it becomes harder and harder to read all the letters before they are covered. Eventually when all the letters are covered the landscapes are walked over and scratched. There is no trace of what was there to start.

Technical / Artistic

The prose is built around a slotted algorithm that builds sentences always starting with a universal pronoun. It then splits and randomizes the lines and fills the allotted grid space it is given. The build up of sentences creates a sort of character study or life.

The landscapes are a set of very simple rolling shapes with texture applied, they stick to a predefined color scheme chosen by the hash. They remind me of tissue paper stained glass kids make in kindergarten.

The scratches are just that, scratches or shapes that bleed through to the background. They serve to flatten and wipe away, chair scratches on a ballroom floor or bird footprints in sand.

---

Scaling the image up or down will yield slightly different final outputs. I prefer the 10:9 view ratio. Right click to save image. 

Just code (Javascript, no frameworks or dependencies).
Made by DSims (dillansimmons.com)
